101	 * an explicit type cast:
102	 *
103	 * drop_chunks('conditions', '2020-10-01'::date);
104	 *
105	 * However, we can handle the UNKNOWNOID case since we have the time type
106	 * information in internal metadata (e.g., the time column type of a
107	 * hypertable) and we can try to convert the argument to that type.
108	 *
109	 * Thus, there are two cases:
110	 *
111	 * 1. An explicit cast was done --> the type is given in argtype.
112	 * 2. No cast was done --> we try to convert the argument to the known time
